Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/25/01 4:07:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revised Vox Strategy and loot rules *please read*</span><hr size=1> One thing I would like to add.<br>
<br>
I trust the people I raid with.  I dont know many of them, but to be fair many dont know me.  Yet they entrust me with their equipment and experience hoping that I know what I'm doing.  All in the name of having a good time.  I think its only fair that everyone therefore have as good a chance as anyone else to potentially get whatever they want.<br>
<br>
The potential for abuse is evident, that is true.  But part of the spirit of KCoG has been to trust and believe in others.  Yes, I know its possible for people to sell the white scale.  Its also possible for them to sell the eyepatch or a cof.  We know it happens, I've seen both for sale in EC.  Yet that doesnt matter.  I know I prefer to believe in the best in people rather than assume the worst.  I may constantly be setting myself up for disappointment and hurt feelings, but occasionally I find someone who cares that makes up for it.<br>
<br>
And as far as use, the white dragonscale cloak is one of the best cloaks a druid can get.  Sure, there are several awesome pieces out of ToV that are better, but most of us will never see those.  So what is more important?  A scale going to a epic quest that may or may not ever be completed and used in a CoG raid, or a scale going to a cloak that may or may not be sold and may help save both the life of the wearer and make them useful to both CoG and their groups in the future?  Of course this is a loaded question, there is no right answer since it all depends on where your looking at.<br>
<br>
One thing to consider.  If you dont like the loot rules you can of course always post here to try to change it.  This may or may not work.  But, there are other options.  You can begin to actually lead these raids.  You lead a Planar raid, you set the loot rules.  You lead a dragon raid, you set the loot rules.  Of course, if you start really restricting the loot dont expect a lot of people to show up since CoG is not an alliance and is not mandatory.  However, the option is always there.  I'm always looking for people to back me up and I'm sure Kommisar wouldnt mind someone to take the occasional raid to reduce his stress level.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Just the ramblings of a druid who finally got kicked out of a room party. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzondro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zondro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/29/01 1:02:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revised Vox Strategy and loot rules *please read*</span><hr size=1> well, I've never been in on a roll or whatever, but here's the thing.  If a scale drops in tonights Vox raid, and i'm there with my bard, I'd feel REALLY guilty if only bards were allowed to roll on the scale because of epic concerns.  Why?  cause there is no way in hell i'd keep it for Steps.  I'd much rather either turn it in for a cloak for Zondro or ecBay it for like 100k.<br>
